cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with face alignment, 3D face reconstruction, and face recognition, which are all topics related to computer vision. Additionally, the use of cascaded regression and mapping matrices are common techniques in computer vision. 

The paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as the proposed method is based on a summation model and uses cascaded regression, which are both machine learning techniques. 

The artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper proposes a method that can automatically generate both pose-and-expression-normalized (PEN) and expressive 3D faces, which requires some level of artificial intelligence. 

The multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category is another possibility as the paper deals with 3D face reconstruction, which is a multimedia-related topic. 

Finally, the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category is a possibility as the paper deals with 3D face reconstruction, which is a graphics-related topic.
